               <p>WILLIAM DANCE. I am a <rs id="t18280410-253-viclabel1352" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-253-victim1405 t18280410-253-viclabel1352"></join>, and worked with the prisoner at an empty house in <placeName id="t18280410-253-crimeloc1353">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-253-crimeloc1353" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-253-crimeloc1353" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-253-off1350 t18280410-253-crimeloc1353"></join>. On the 26th of February, I left my mallet there, and missed it in the morning; I found it in the room where the prisoner lives a fortnight after; he was apprehended by my master for robbing him, but the bill was thrown out - I lost some other tools about that time - another man worked there with us.</p>

               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Were you on the premises at the time you lost the mallet? A. No: after he was apprehended, his wife came there for some tools of his.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-253-person1406">
                  FRANCIS 
                  FAGAN
               <interp inst="t18280410-253-person1406" type="surname" value="FAGAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-253-person1406" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-253-person1406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner on the the 29th of February. Dance afterwards came to my house, and said he had lost a mallet; we went to the prisoner's room, and found a great many tools - Dance picked this mallet out.</p>
